@NODE "ReadConfig()" "Config: ReadConfig()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     ReadConfig()
Short:    Reads one selected string from a configuration file.
Synopsis: BYTE * ReadConfig(*Config [a0], BYTE *Section [a1],
            BYTE *Item [a2]);

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  function allows you to search a Config object for an item or array of
data.   To  demonstrate, look at the following config header from source/c/
misc/test.cnf:

  [Map]
  Terrain=JUNGLE
  X=16
  Y=16
  Width=96
  Height=96

  [MapData]
  =sdmi@46af2nAGvod//39/dssfji3355
  =dvmAKJva35900vo36mAGJILSmdmm392

To read the terrain string, you would use this function call:

  str = ReadConfig(Config,"Map","Terrain");

To read the map array data:

  str = ReadConfig(Config,"MapData",NULL);

To read integer items such as the Width, you must use ReadConfigInt().

Note  that  array  Sections  do  not  contain individual items (see MapData
example), so a setting of NULL in the Item argument is appropriate in these
cases.

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
Config
  Pointer to an initialised Config object.

Section
  A string specifying the section that you want to look at.

Item
  The specific item that contains the string you want to retrieve.

@{b}@{u}RESULT@{uu}@{ub}
Returns  a  string pointing to the data or NULL if unsuccessful.  Note that
the  string  is  READ-ONLY  and cannot be tampered with.  Use StrClone() or
StrCopy() in the strings module if you want to move the data to a writeable
location.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Config: @{"ReadConfigInt()" LINK "ReadConfigInt()"}

@EndNode
