@NODE "ReadConfigInt()" "Config: ReadConfigInt()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     ReadConfigInt()
Short:    Reads one selected string from a configuration file.
Synopsis: LONG ReadConfigInt(*Config [a0], BYTE *Section [a1],
            BYTE *Item [a2]);

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  function  is  almost  identical to ReadConfig(), but it will return a
converted integer rather than a string.

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
Config
  Pointer to an initialised Config object.

Section
  A string specifying the section that you want to look at.

Item
  The specific item that contains the integer you want to retrieve.

@{b}@{u}RESULT@{uu}@{ub}
Returns  the  integer  value  or  NULL  if  the integer is 0 or there was a
failure.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Config: @{"ReadConfig()" LINK "ReadConfig()"}

@EndNode
